10 POLICY COMMITTEE RECOMMENDATION
11 An Act relating to teachers; amending 70 O.S. 2021,
Section 6-195, as amended by Section 4, Chapter 15,
12 O.S.L. 2023 (70 O.S. Supp. 2025, Section 6-195),
which relates to an induction program; stating that
13 the program is state-supported; providing program
purposes; updating date references; providing
14 possible funding sources; allowing promulgation of
necessary rules; providing an effective date; and
15 declaring an emergency.
16
17
18 BE IT ENACTED BY THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF OKLAHOMA:
19 SECTION 1. AMENDATORY 70 O.S. 2021, Section 6-195, as
20 amended by Section 4, Chapter 15, O.S.L. 2023 (70 O.S. Supp. 2025,
21 Section 6-195), is amended to read as follows:
22 Section 6-195. A. As funds are available, the State Department
23 of Education in consultation with the Office of Educational Quality
24 and Accountability shall administer an a state-supported teacher
Req. No. 17355 Page 1

1 indu ction program for teachers which shall be approved by the State
2 Board of Education. The program shall support first-year teachers
3 through professional development, mentorship, and instructional
4 coaching designed to improve teacher effectiveness and retention.
5 Beginning with the 2015-2016 2026-2027 school year, each school
6 district shall participate in the induction program. The program
7 shall include, but not be limited to:
8 1. Guidance to school districts for successful induction
9 programs;
10 2. Training for school districts to include the selection,
11 function and duties of mentors; and
12 3. Resources for appropriate professional development, support,
13 mentorship and coaching for the inductee and mentors.
14 B. Funding for the induction program may include legislative
15 appropriations, grants, and contributions from philanthropic
16 organizations, nonprofit entities, or other external partners. Such
17 partnerships may supplement state funding when state funds are
18 limited or unavailable.
19 C. The induction program training shall be completed at a
20 frequency as determined by the board State Board of education
21 Education.
22 C. D. The State Board of Education may promulgate rules
23 necessary for administration of the induction program.
24 SECTION 2. This act shall become effective July 1, 2026.
Req. No. 17355 Page 2

1 SECTION 3. It being immediately necessary for the preservation
2 of the public peace, health, or safety, an emergency is hereby
3 declared to exist, by reason whereof this act shall take effect and
4 be in full force from and after its passage and approval.
